    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-02T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-02T13:00:00-05:00" n="1128"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1128">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.79658/713: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé to the Norwegian Government in Exile</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-02T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 2, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 2—6:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Norwegian Series. Foreign Minister Lie<note n="30" xml:id="d1128fn30">Trygve
                        Lie, Norwegian Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> assures me orally (and
                    will confirm by letter) that Norwegian Government desires operation of the
                    American air service described in your 802, February 1, 9 p.m. and states
                    appropriate instructions will be sent immediately to Colonel Berg, Norwegian
                    Military Attaché at Stockholm. He asks me to convey Norwegian Government’s
                    deepest appreciation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
